		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Don't panic Tepples, the licenced famicom game "Portpia Renzoku Satsujin Jiken" by Enix did the same, rely on $2002 polling rather than normal NMI handling. Since the game works all trough menus (it was basically programmed to test how the japaneese audience was liking menu-based games, as a prior to Dragon Quest), the only real issue of this would be the cursor blinking less smoothly.

		

